/**
 * Middleware function to handle file access permissions.
 *
 * @param \Illuminate\Http\Request $request
 * @param \Closure $next
 * @return mixed
 */
public function handle($request, Closure $next)
{
    $user_id = $request->user()->id;
    $folder_id = $request->user()->userable->getFolderId();
    $is_folder = strpos($request->file, $request->user()->userable->getFolderName());

    if ($user_id == $folder_id && $is_folder !== false) {
        return $next($request);
    } else {
        return abort(404);
    }
}
```

In the solution, the `handle` function receives the request object and a closure. It retrieves the user ID and folder ID from the request object and checks if the file path contains the user's folder name. If both the user ID and folder ID match, and the file path contains the folder name, the function allows access by calling the provided closure. Otherwise, it returns a 404 error.

